Description: A single key function, 'Require' that makes rerun-tolerant
    versions of 'install.packages' and 'require' for CRAN packages,
    packages no longer on CRAN (i.e., archived), specific versions of
    packages, and GitHub packages. This approach is developed to create
    reproducible workflows that are flexible and fast enough to use while
    in development stages, while able to build snapshots once a stable
    package collection is found.  As with other functions in a
    reproducible workflow, this package emphasizes functions that return
    the same result whether it is the first or subsequent times running
    the function, with subsequent times being sufficiently fast that they
    can be run every time without undue waiting burden on the user or
    developer.
